cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY

This paper investigates the vulnerability of LTE to intentional jamming, which falls under the category of network security and communication. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper analyzes the components of the LTE downlink and uplink signals, which involves signal processing and modulation techniques, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the physical layer of LTE, which involves wireless communication and signal processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper aims to establish the overall vulnerability of LTE to hostile interference, which involves system-level analysis and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category as well.
